Method Detail

intersect

public CCRange intersect(CCRange ccRange)
Description copied from interface: CCRange
Intersection of the current range of control commands with another one.

Priority of current range must be greater than priority of another range, otherwise principles of control command evaluation may be violated. Method will throw an exception in this case.

Priority of the intersection will be equal to lowest priority.

Specified by:
intersect in interface CCRange
Parameters:
ccRange - range of control command to intersect with
Returns:
new instance of CCRange that represents intersection of this and another ccRange. Priority of resulted ccRange will be equal to lowest one of priorities.
